com.google.cloud.compute

Class MachineType

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.google.cloud.compute.MachineType
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Serializable

    public class MachineType
extends Object
implements Serializable
    A Google Compute Engine machine type. A machine type determine the virtualized hardware specifications of your virtual machine instances, such as the amount of memory or number of virtual CPUs.
    See Also:
    Machine Types, Serialized Form

      • deprecationStatus

        @Deprecated
public DeprecationStatus<MachineTypeId> deprecationStatus()
        Deprecated. 
        Returns the deprecation status of the machine type. If DeprecationStatus.status() is either DeprecationStatus.Status.DELETED or DeprecationStatus.Status.OBSOLETE the machine type should not be used. Returns null if the machine type is not deprecated.

      • getDeprecationStatus

        Returns the deprecation status of the machine type. If DeprecationStatus.status() is either DeprecationStatus.Status.DELETED or DeprecationStatus.Status.OBSOLETE the machine type should not be used. Returns null if the machine type is not deprecated.
